`admin-user` so MongoDB stores only SHA-256 credentials:\n   ```javascript\n   db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n     mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n     pwd: \"<new-password>\"\n   });\n   ```\n4. Roll the StatefulSet one pod at a time (see Section 4 for order).\n\n### 3.2 Enforce Least-Privilege Roles\n\n**Why:** A single credential combining `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, and\n`readWriteAnyDatabase` violates least privilege. Compromise of this one account\nyields full cluster control and unrestricted data access simultaneously.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Create separate purpose-scoped accounts:\n   - `dba-cluster` → `clusterAdmin` only (replica-set and sharding operations)\n   - `dba-users` → `userAdminAnyDatabase` only (user lifecycle management)\n   - Per-application service accounts → `readWrite` scoped to specific databases\n2. Update Kubernetes Secrets and application config to reference the new accounts.\n3. After verifying all consumers work, revoke the broad roles from `admin-user`\n   or drop the account entirely.\n\n### 3.3 Enable TLS for All Connections\n\n**Why:** Without TLS, client traffic and inter-member replication are plaintext.\nThe keyFile provides mutual authentication between members but no encryption.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Issue a CA certificate and per-member server certificates, one SAN per pod\n   DNS name (e.g., `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`).\n   Store the CA cert, combined cert+key PEM, in a new Secret (e.g., `mongo-tls-certs`).\n2. Mount the Secret as a volume in the StatefulSet at `/etc/mongo-tls/`.\n3. Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n   ```yaml\n   net:\n     tls:\n       mode: requireTLS\n       certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n       CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n   ```\n4. Two-phase rolling restart to avoid split-brain during transition:\n   - Phase 1: set `mode: allowTLS` → roll all three pods → confirm all SECONDARY.\n   - Phase 2: set `mode: requireTLS` → roll all three pods again.\n5. After TLS is enforced, optionally migrate internal auth from keyFile to x.509\n   (`security.clusterAuthMode: x509`) to retire the `mongo-keyfile` Secret.\n\n### 3.4 Restrict Network Binding\n\n**Why:** Binding to all interfaces exposes mongod unnecessarily. Inside Kubernetes\nthe pod IP is sufficient for service mesh and headless-service connectivity.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Replace `net.bindIpAll: true` with an explicit `net.bindIp` in `mongod-config`.\n   Inject the pod IP via a Downward API env var in the StatefulSet:\n   ```yaml\n   env:\n     - name: POD_IP\n       valueFrom:\n         fieldRef:\n           fieldPath: status.podIP\n   ```\n   Then in `mongod.conf`:\n   ```yaml\n   net:\n     bindIp: 127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\n   ```\n2. Apply a `NetworkPolicy` in the `mongodb` namespace allowing ingress on port\n   27017 only from authorized application namespaces; deny all other ingress.\n\n### 3.5 Lower Log Verbosity to 0\n\n**Why:** `verbosity: 1` floods logs with internal debug output, inflating storage\ncosts and burying real warnings and errors.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Edit `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n   ```yaml\n   systemLog:\n     verbosity: 0\n   ```\n2. Can also be applied live without pod restart (on each member):\n   ```javascript\n   db.adminCommand({ setParameter: 1, logLevel: 0 });\n   ```\n\n### 3.6 Tighten Slow-Operation Threshold to 50 ms\n\n**Why:** At 200 ms, queries degrading into the 50–200 ms range — a common early\nindicator of missing indexes or lock contention — go undetected. A 50 ms threshold\ngives earlier warning.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Edit `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n   ```yaml\n   operationProfiling:\n     mode: slowOp\n     slowOpThresholdMs: 50\n   ```\n2. Can also be applied live (on each member):\n   ```javascript\n   db.adminCommand({ setParameter: 1, slowOpThresholdMs: 50 });\n   ```\n3. After applying, review `db.system.profile` to gauge baseline query health\n   before committing the tighter threshold permanently.\n\n### 3.7 Migrate Journal Compressor from `zlib` to `snappy`\n\n**Why:** `zlib` is CPU-intensive. `snappy` decompresses ~5× faster at a modest\nreduction in compression ratio — a better trade-off for write-heavy OLTP workloads.\n(`zstd` is a valid third option: better ratio than snappy, lower CPU than zlib,\navailable in MongoDB 4.2+.)\n\n**Warning:** WiredTiger's compressor is a storage-engine setting. Existing on-disk\ndata is not recompressed on config change — new blocks written after the restart\nuse the new compressor. A full initial sync is required on each member to\nrecompress all data uniformly.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n1. Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n   ```yaml\n   storage:\n     wiredTiger:\n       engineConfig:\n         journalCompressor: snappy\n   ```\n2. Roll each member through a fresh initial sync:\n   - Temporarily set `priority: 0, votes: 0` for the target member via\n     `rs.reconfig()` to isolate it.\n   - Delete the pod; let it rejoin and perform an initial sync from a healthy\n     member that already has the new compressor config.\n   - Verify member reaches `SECONDARY` before proceeding to the next.\n   - Repeat for the remaining secondary, then step down the primary and repeat.\n3. Restore original `priority` and `votes` values via `rs.reconfig()` when done.\n\n### 3.8 Raise Default Write Concern to `majority`\n\n**Why:** The current default `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` acknowledges writes from the\nprimary alone. On primary failover, in-flight writes that reached only the primary\nare lost. `w: majority` ensures data is durable on at least 2 of 3 members before\nthe client receives acknowledgement.\n\n**Steps (do not apply now):**\n```javascript\ncfg = rs.conf();\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 };\nrs.reconfig(cfg);\n```\nAlternatively, enforce majority durability at the application layer via connection\nstring parameters (`?w=majority&wtimeoutMS=5000`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Execution Order and Dependencies\n\nChanges must be sequenced to avoid outages or inconsistent intermediate states:\n\n| Step | Change | Method | Downtime |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Lower log verbosity (3.5) | Live `setParameter` per member | None |\n| 2 | Tighten slow-op threshold (3.6) | Live `setParameter` per member | None |\n| 3 | Restrict network binding + NetworkPolicy (3.4) | Rolling pod restart | None (rolling) |\n| 4 | TLS phase 1: `allowTLS` (3.3) | Rolling restart with cert mounts | None (rolling) |\n| 5 | Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 (3.1) | Config + user update, rolling restart | None (rolling) |\n| 6 | TLS phase 2: `requireTLS` (3.3) | Rolling restart | None (rolling) |\n| 7 | Least-privilege users (3.2) | Live user admin | None |\n| 8 | Majority write concern (3.8) | Live `rs.reconfig()` | None |\n| 9 | Journal compressor migration (3.7) | Full rolling initial sync | None (rolling, slow) |\n\nSteps 1–2 are non-disruptive and can serve as a low-risk warm-up before the\nformal change window. Step 9 is the most time-consuming and should be scheduled\nas a separate maintenance window with a storage backup in hand.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Notes\n\n- **Config changes (verbosity, threshold):** revert `mongod-config` ConfigMap and\n  restart affected pods; or apply live via `setParameter` in reverse.\n- **TLS:** revert `requireTLS` → `allowTLS` → remove `net.tls` block, two rolling\n  restarts. Client applications must also remove TLS connection config.\n- **Journal compressor:** once a member has written blocks with `snappy`, those\n  blocks cannot be read by a `zlib`-only mongod. Ensure all members complete the\n  initial sync before writing new application data under the new compressor. Keep\n  a volume snapshot or `mongodump` backup before starting Step 9.\n- **User changes:** preserve the original `admin-user` Secret until all new\n  service accounts are confirmed working in production.\n\n---\n\n*This document is for change-window planning only. The live cluster has not been modified.*\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":378,"newStart":1,"newLines":284,"lines":["-# Elasticsearch Cluster Upgrade & Migration Plan","+# MongoDB Replica Set — Change & Migration Plan"," ","-**Prepared:** 2026-06-25  ","-**Cluster:** `es-cluster` (namespace: `elasticsearch`)  ","-**Current version:** 8.11.1  ","-**Target version:** 8.17.x (latest stable 8.x release)  ","-**Scope:** Planning only — no live changes until this plan is approved.","+**Date:** 2026-06-25  ","+**Cluster namespace:** `mongodb`  ","+**Replica set name:** `mongodb-replica`  ","+**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — no changes applied to the live cluster."," "," ---"," "," ## 1. Current State Inventory"," ","-### 1.1 Cluster Topology","+### 1.1 Replica Set Topology"," ","-| Item | Value |","-|------|-------|","-| Cluster name | es-cluster |","-| Node count | 3 (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2) |","-| Node roles | master + data + ingest (all nodes, no role separation) |","-| Node tier attribute | `node.attr.tier: hot` (uniform) |","-| Pod management | `Parallel` |","-| Update strategy | `OnDelete` (manual pod deletion required to trigger rollout) |","-| Termination grace period | 30 s |","+| Member | Host | Priority | Votes | Arbiter | Hidden |","+|---|---|---|---|---|---|","+| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | no | no |","+| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | no | no |","+| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | no | no |"," ","-### 1.2 Container Image and Resources","+- Protocol version: 1 (Raft)","+- `writeConcernMajorityJournalDefault`: true","+- All three members are equal-priority data-bearing nodes; primary is elected by the set.","+- Default write concern: `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` (primary acknowledgement only)."," ","-| Item | Value |","-|------|-------|","-| Image | `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1` |","-| CPU request / limit | 500 m / 1 CPU |","-| Memory request / limit | 1 Gi / 2 Gi |","-| JVM heap | -Xms512m -Xmx512m (fixed, G1GC) |","-| GC collector | G1 Young/Old/Concurrent |","-| Storage per node | 5 Gi PVC (ReadWriteOnce) |","-| OpenJDK version | 21.0.1 (bundled) |","+### 1.2 Users and Roles"," ","-### 1.3 Elasticsearch Configuration (`es-config` ConfigMap)","+| User | DB | Roles |","+|---|---|---|","+| `admin-user` | `admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |"," ","-```yaml","-cluster.name: es-cluster","-node.name: ${POD_NAME}","-node.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]","-node.attr.tier: hot","-network.host: 0.0.0.0","-discovery.seed_hosts:","-  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster","-  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster","-  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster","-cluster.initial_master_nodes:","-  - es-cluster-0","-  - es-cluster-1","-  - es-cluster-2","-node.store.allow_mmap: false","-xpack.security.enabled: false","-xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false","-xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false","-```","+- Authentication mechanisms active: **SCRAM-SHA-1** and **SCRAM-SHA-256** (both enabled).","+- Password stored in Kubernetes Secret `admin-user-password`."," ","-### 1.4 Cluster Settings","+### 1.3 Storage — Journal Compressor"," ","-- **Persistent settings:** none (all defaults)  ","-- **Transient settings:** none  ","-- Notable defaults in effect: `cluster.routing.allocation.type: desired_balance`, disk watermarks at 85/90/95%, `cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000`.","+WiredTiger journal compressor: **`zlib`**  ","+(set via `mongod-config` ConfigMap → `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor`)"," ","-### 1.5 Cluster Health","+### 1.4 Log Verbosity"," ","-- **Status:** green  ","-- Active shards: 6 (3 primary + 3 replica)  ","-- Pending tasks at inspection: 60 (likely election-related backlog on a fresh cluster)","+`systemLog.verbosity: 1` — raised above the MongoDB default (`0`).  ","+Produces extra diagnostic output for all components globally."," ","-### 1.6 Indices","+### 1.5 Slow-Operation Threshold"," ","-| Index | Shards | Replicas | Shard allocation |","-|-------|--------|----------|-----------------|","-| audit-index | 3 | 1 | `require.tier: hot`, `_tier_preference: data_content` |","+`operationProfiling.mode: slowOp`, `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 200`  ","+The MongoDB default is 100 ms. The current value of 200 ms is less sensitive than","+the default — operations completing between 100 ms and 200 ms are not flagged."," ","-No data streams, ILM policies, or index templates are associated with user-managed indices. All ILM policies present are built-in Elastic-managed policies (`managed: true`).","+### 1.6 Network Binding"," ","-### 1.7 Security Posture","+`net.bindIpAll: true` — mongod listens on all pod interfaces (0.0.0.0)."," ","-| Setting | Value | Risk |","-|---------|-------|------|","-| `xpack.security.enabled` | **false** | CRITICAL — unauthenticated access |","-| HTTP SSL | **false** | Plaintext traffic |","-| Transport SSL | **false** | Plaintext inter-node traffic |","-| Audit logging | false | No access audit trail |","+### 1.7 TLS/SSL"," ","+Not configured. Client-to-server and inter-member replication traffic are","+unencrypted. Internal member authentication relies on a shared `keyFile` Secret","+(`mongo-keyfile`), which provides mutual auth but no encryption in transit.","+"," ---"," ","-## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist","+## 2. Target Hardened Baseline"," ","-These items must be verified and resolved **before** the upgrade window begins.","+| Area | Current | Target |","+|---|---|---|","+| Auth mechanisms | SCRAM-SHA-1 + SCRAM-SHA-256 | SCRAM-SHA-256 only |","+| Privilege model | One super-account with 3 broad roles | Least-privilege: one account per function |","+| TLS | None | `requireTLS` for clients and inter-member traffic |","+| Network binding | All interfaces (`0.0.0.0`) | Pod IP + loopback; NetworkPolicy for port 27017 |","+| Log verbosity | `1` | `0` (production default) |","+| Slow-op threshold | `200 ms` | `50 ms` (catch more degraded queries) |","+| Journal compressor | `zlib` | `snappy` (lower CPU overhead) |","+| Default write concern | `{ w: 1 }` | `{ w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }` |"," ","-### 2.1 CRITICAL — Enable Security (Blocking)","-","-Elasticsearch 8.x ships with security disabled only when auto-configured on the initial bootstrap; leaving it off permanently in production is unsupported and a compliance risk. **Security must be enabled before upgrading** because:","-","-- Later 8.x releases tighten default security enforcement.","-- The upgrade process itself accesses internal system indices; without security, there is no isolation between internal and user traffic.","-- Any migration to Elasticsearch 9.x will require security to be enabled.","-","-**Required changes to `es-config`:**","-","-```yaml","-# Remove or change these three lines:","-xpack.security.enabled: false          # change to: true","-xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false # change to: true (or configure with certificates)","-xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false # change to: true","-```","-","-Steps to enable security on a running cluster:","-","-1. Generate or obtain TLS certificates for HTTP and transport layers (self-signed CA is acceptable for transport; a valid cert is recommended for HTTP).","-2. Mount the certificates into each pod (add a Secret-backed volume to the StatefulSet).","-3. Update `es-config` with certificate paths and enable security settings.","-4. Perform a full rolling restart (one pod at a time) to apply the new config **before** the version upgrade.","-5. Set the built-in `elastic` superuser password:  ","-   `bin/elasticsearch-reset-password -u elastic`","-6. Update any clients (Kibana, application code) with the new credentials and HTTPS endpoints.","-","-### 2.2 Resolve Pending Task Queue","-","-At inspection the cluster had **60 pending tasks**. Before upgrading:","-","-```bash","-kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\","-  curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/pending_tasks?v\"","-```","-","-Investigate and resolve any stuck tasks. A high queue depth during an upgrade can cause split-brain or delayed shard re-assignment.","-","-### 2.3 Snapshot Backup","-","-Create a registered snapshot repository and take a full snapshot of all indices before any change:","-","-```bash","-# Register a repository (adjust type/settings to match your storage backend)","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_snapshot/backup_repo\" \\","-  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{","-    \"type\": \"fs\",","-    \"settings\": { \"location\": \"/mnt/snapshots\" }","-  }'","-","-# Take snapshot","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_snapshot/backup_repo/pre-upgrade-8.11.1\"","-```","-","-Verify the snapshot completes successfully before proceeding.","-","-### 2.4 Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` After First Bootstrap","-","-The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting must be **removed from the config file** after the cluster has completed its initial bootstrapping. Keeping it in place is harmless on a stable cluster but is flagged as a deprecation warning in newer 8.x releases and must be absent for any node that restarts during the upgrade.","-","-**Change to `es-config`:**  ","-Remove the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` block entirely.","-","-### 2.5 Shard Allocation Constraint Review","-","-`audit-index` has:","-- `index.routing.allocation.require.tier: hot`","-- `index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference: data_content`","-","-All three nodes are tagged `node.attr.tier: hot`, so all shards can allocate to any node. This is safe for a rolling upgrade. No changes needed, but **verify allocation is still green** after each node restart during the upgrade.","-","-### 2.6 Storage Headroom","-","-Each node has 5 Gi PVC. Elasticsearch performs segment merges during recovery. Confirm available disk space on each PVC:","-","-```bash","-kubectl -n elasticsearch exec es-cluster-0 -- df -h /usr/share/elasticsearch/data","-```","-","-Recommended minimum free space: 20% headroom, or at least 1 Gi above current index size.","-","-### 2.7 Heap Size Assessment","-","-Current heap: 512 MB. The 50%-of-container-memory rule (1 Gi request / 2 Gi limit) is not being followed — heap is sized below 50% of the request. For a data node this may cause frequent GC pressure under moderate load.","-","-**Recommended change:**  ","-Raise heap to at least `1g` (`-Xms1g -Xmx1g`) and increase the Pod memory request/limit proportionally:","-","-```yaml","-# StatefulSet env","-- name: ES_JAVA_OPTS","-  value: \"-Xms1g -Xmx1g\"","-# resources","-resources:","-  requests:","-    cpu: \"500m\"","-    memory: \"2Gi\"","-  limits:","-    cpu: \"2\"","-    memory: \"4Gi\"","-```","-","-Apply this in the same rolling restart used to enable security — not a separate disruption.","-"," ---"," ","-## 3. Upgrade Procedure (8.11.1 → 8.17.x)","+## 3. Required Changes"," ","-This is a **rolling upgrade** (no cluster downtime) within the 8.x major series. All 8.x nodes are wire-compatible down to 7.17.0, so a mixed-version cluster is tolerated during the transition.","+### 3.1 Disable SCRAM-SHA-1"," ","-### Step 1 — Disable Shard Allocation (before each pod restart)","+**Why:** SCRAM-SHA-1 is cryptographically weaker than SCRAM-SHA-256. All MongoDB 6.0","+client drivers support SHA-256; retaining SHA-1 is unnecessary attack surface."," ","-```bash","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\","-  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{","-    \"persistent\": {","-      \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"","-    }","-  }'","-```","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Confirm all application connection strings use drivers that support SCRAM-SHA-256.","+2. Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap to restrict accepted mechanisms:","+   ```yaml","+   security:","+     authorization: enabled","+     keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile","+     authenticationMechanisms: SCRAM-SHA-256","+   ```","+3. Re-provision `admin-user` so MongoDB stores only SHA-256 credentials:","+   ```javascript","+   db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {","+     mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],","+     pwd: \"<new-password>\"","+   });","+   ```","+4. Roll the StatefulSet one pod at a time (see Section 4 for order)."," ","-This prevents Elasticsearch from re-balancing shards during the brief period a node is offline.","+### 3.2 Enforce Least-Privilege Roles"," ","-### Step 2 — Perform a Synced Flush","+**Why:** A single credential combining `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, and","+`readWriteAnyDatabase` violates least privilege. Compromise of this one account","+yields full cluster control and unrestricted data access simultaneously."," ","-```bash","-curl -X POST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_flush\"","-```","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Create separate purpose-scoped accounts:","+   - `dba-cluster` → `clusterAdmin` only (replica-set and sharding operations)","+   - `dba-users` → `userAdminAnyDatabase` only (user lifecycle management)","+   - Per-application service accounts → `readWrite` scoped to specific databases","+2. Update Kubernetes Secrets and application config to reference the new accounts.","+3. After verifying all consumers work, revoke the broad roles from `admin-user`","+   or drop the account entirely."," ","-Synced flush marks shard copies as consistent, which speeds up recovery after the node restarts.","+### 3.3 Enable TLS for All Connections"," ","-### Step 3 — Update the StatefulSet Image","+**Why:** Without TLS, client traffic and inter-member replication are plaintext.","+The keyFile provides mutual authentication between members but no encryption."," ","-Edit the StatefulSet to target the new image:","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Issue a CA certificate and per-member server certificates, one SAN per pod","+   DNS name (e.g., `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`).","+   Store the CA cert, combined cert+key PEM, in a new Secret (e.g., `mongo-tls-certs`).","+2. Mount the Secret as a volume in the StatefulSet at `/etc/mongo-tls/`.","+3. Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+   ```yaml","+   net:","+     tls:","+       mode: requireTLS","+       certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem","+       CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt","+   ```","+4. Two-phase rolling restart to avoid split-brain during transition:","+   - Phase 1: set `mode: allowTLS` → roll all three pods → confirm all SECONDARY.","+   - Phase 2: set `mode: requireTLS` → roll all three pods again.","+5. After TLS is enforced, optionally migrate internal auth from keyFile to x.509","+   (`security.clusterAuthMode: x509`) to retire the `mongo-keyfile` Secret."," ","-```bash","-kubectl -n elasticsearch patch statefulset es-cluster \\","-  --type='json' \\","-  -p='[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/image\",","-         \"value\":\"docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.17.x\"}]'","-```","+### 3.4 Restrict Network Binding"," ","-Because `updateStrategy: OnDelete`, the StatefulSet will **not** restart any pods automatically.","+**Why:** Binding to all interfaces exposes mongod unnecessarily. Inside Kubernetes","+the pod IP is sufficient for service mesh and headless-service connectivity."," ","-### Step 4 — Rolling Pod Deletion (one at a time)","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Replace `net.bindIpAll: true` with an explicit `net.bindIp` in `mongod-config`.","+   Inject the pod IP via a Downward API env var in the StatefulSet:","+   ```yaml","+   env:","+     - name: POD_IP","+       valueFrom:","+         fieldRef:","+           fieldPath: status.podIP","+   ```","+   Then in `mongod.conf`:","+   ```yaml","+   net:","+     bindIp: 127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)","+   ```","+2. Apply a `NetworkPolicy` in the `mongodb` namespace allowing ingress on port","+   27017 only from authorized application namespaces; deny all other ingress."," ","-Delete pods in reverse ordinal order (es-cluster-2 first, es-cluster-0 last) to minimise master disruption:","+### 3.5 Lower Log Verbosity to 0"," ","-```bash","-# Repeat for each pod: 2, 1, 0","-kubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2","-# Wait for the pod to become Ready before continuing:","-kubectl -n elasticsearch wait pod/es-cluster-2 --for=condition=Ready --timeout=300s","-# Re-enable shard allocation, wait for green:","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\","-  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\","-  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}'","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=120s\"","-# Verify the restarted node is on the new version:","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"","-# Disable allocation again before the next pod:","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\","-  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\","-  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"}}'","-# Then: kubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-1","-# Then: kubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-0","-```","+**Why:** `verbosity: 1` floods logs with internal debug output, inflating storage","+costs and burying real warnings and errors."," ","-### Step 5 — Re-enable Full Shard Allocation","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Edit `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+   ```yaml","+   systemLog:","+     verbosity: 0","+   ```","+2. Can also be applied live without pod restart (on each member):","+   ```javascript","+   db.adminCommand({ setParameter: 1, logLevel: 0 });","+   ```"," ","-After all three pods are updated and the cluster is green:","+### 3.6 Tighten Slow-Operation Threshold to 50 ms"," ","-```bash","-curl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\","-  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\","-  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}'","-```","+**Why:** At 200 ms, queries degrading into the 50–200 ms range — a common early","+indicator of missing indexes or lock contention — go undetected. A 50 ms threshold","+gives earlier warning."," ","-### Step 6 — Post-Upgrade Verification","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Edit `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+   ```yaml","+   operationProfiling:","+     mode: slowOp","+     slowOpThresholdMs: 50","+   ```","+2. Can also be applied live (on each member):","+   ```javascript","+   db.adminCommand({ setParameter: 1, slowOpThresholdMs: 50 });","+   ```","+3. After applying, review `db.system.profile` to gauge baseline query health","+   before committing the tighter threshold permanently."," ","-```bash","-# Cluster health","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?pretty\"","-# All nodes on new version","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master,disk.avail\"","-# Index health","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/indices?v&h=index,health,status,pri,rep,docs.count\"","-# No unassigned shards","-curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/shards?v\" | grep UNASSIGNED","-```","+### 3.7 Migrate Journal Compressor from `zlib` to `snappy`"," ","----","+**Why:** `zlib` is CPU-intensive. `snappy` decompresses ~5× faster at a modest","+reduction in compression ratio — a better trade-off for write-heavy OLTP workloads.","+(`zstd` is a valid third option: better ratio than snappy, lower CPU than zlib,","+available in MongoDB 4.2+.)"," ","-## 4. Configuration Changes Required in `es-config`","+**Warning:** WiredTiger's compressor is a storage-engine setting. Existing on-disk","+data is not recompressed on config change — new blocks written after the restart","+use the new compressor. A full initial sync is required on each member to","+recompress all data uniformly."," ","-Summarised list of all ConfigMap changes needed (to be applied as a pre-upgrade config restart, before the image upgrade):","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+1. Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+   ```yaml","+   storage:","+     wiredTiger:","+       engineConfig:","+         journalCompressor: snappy","+   ```","+2. Roll each member through a fresh initial sync:","+   - Temporarily set `priority: 0, votes: 0` for the target member via","+     `rs.reconfig()` to isolate it.","+   - Delete the pod; let it rejoin and perform an initial sync from a healthy","+     member that already has the new compressor config.","+   - Verify member reaches `SECONDARY` before proceeding to the next.","+   - Repeat for the remaining secondary, then step down the primary and repeat.","+3. Restore original `priority` and `votes` values via `rs.reconfig()` when done."," ","-```yaml","-# Changes to elasticsearch.yml:","+### 3.8 Raise Default Write Concern to `majority`"," ","-# 1. Enable security (CRITICAL)","-xpack.security.enabled: true","-xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true","-xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true","+**Why:** The current default `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` acknowledges writes from the","+primary alone. On primary failover, in-flight writes that reached only the primary","+are lost. `w: majority` ensures data is durable on at least 2 of 3 members before","+the client receives acknowledgement."," ","-# 2. Add certificate paths (after generating/mounting certs)","-xpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/http.p12","-xpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/transport.p12","-xpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/transport.p12","-","-# 3. Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes (cluster already bootstrapped)","-# DELETE the following lines:","-# cluster.initial_master_nodes:","-#   - es-cluster-0","-#   - es-cluster-1","-#   - es-cluster-2","+**Steps (do not apply now):**","+```javascript","+cfg = rs.conf();","+cfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 };","+rs.reconfig(cfg);"," ```","+Alternatively, enforce majority durability at the application layer via connection","+string parameters (`?w=majority&wtimeoutMS=5000`)."," "," ---"," ","-## 5. Node Role Separation (Recommended for Future Growth)","+## 4. Execution Order and Dependencies"," ","-Currently all three nodes are `[master, data, ingest]`. This is acceptable for a three-node cluster but introduces risk as the cluster grows: a data-heavy node can starve the master election process.","+Changes must be sequenced to avoid outages or inconsistent intermediate states:"," ","-**Recommended future architecture (requires adding nodes first):**","+| Step | Change | Method | Downtime |","+|---|---|---|---|","+| 1 | Lower log verbosity (3.5) | Live `setParameter` per member | None |","+| 2 | Tighten slow-op threshold (3.6) | Live `setParameter` per member | None |","+| 3 | Restrict network binding + NetworkPolicy (3.4) | Rolling pod restart | None (rolling) |","+| 4 | TLS phase 1: `allowTLS` (3.3) | Rolling restart with cert mounts | None (rolling) |","+| 5 | Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 (3.1) | Config + user update, rolling restart | None (rolling) |","+| 6 | TLS phase 2: `requireTLS` (3.3) | Rolling restart | None (rolling) |","+| 7 | Least-privilege users (3.2) | Live user admin | None |","+| 8 | Majority write concern (3.8) | Live `rs.reconfig()` | None |","+| 9 | Journal compressor migration (3.7) | Full rolling initial sync | None (rolling, slow) |"," ","-| Nodes | Roles |","-|-------|-------|","-| es-cluster-0..2 (existing) | `data`, `ingest` |","-| es-master-0..2 (new, small pods) | `master` only (voting_only for 2 of them) |","+Steps 1–2 are non-disruptive and can serve as a low-risk warm-up before the","+formal change window. Step 9 is the most time-consuming and should be scheduled","+as a separate maintenance window with a storage backup in hand."," ","-This separation is **not required for this upgrade cycle** but should be planned before scaling beyond 5 data nodes.","-"," ---"," ","-## 6. ILM / Index Template Recommendations","+## 5. Rollback Notes"," ","-No user ILM policies are currently active. The `audit-index` has no lifecycle policy attached, meaning its data will accumulate indefinitely.","+- **Config changes (verbosity, threshold):** revert `mongod-config` ConfigMap and","+  restart affected pods; or apply live via `setParameter` in reverse.","+- **TLS:** revert `requireTLS` → `allowTLS` → remove `net.tls` block, two rolling","+  restarts. Client applications must also remove TLS connection config.","+- **Journal compressor:** once a member has written blocks with `snappy`, those","+  blocks cannot be read by a `zlib`-only mongod. Ensure all members complete the","+  initial sync before writing new application data under the new compressor. Keep","+  a volume snapshot or `mongodump` backup before starting Step 9.","+- **User changes:** preserve the original `admin-user` Secret until all new","+  service accounts are confirmed working in production."," ","-**Action items for post-upgrade:**","-","-1. Create an ILM policy for `audit-index` with a retention window appropriate for compliance requirements (e.g., 90 days delete, 7-day warm with forcemerge).","-2. Attach the policy: `PUT /audit-index/_settings {\"index.lifecycle.name\": \"<policy-name>\"}`.","-3. Consider converting `audit-index` to a data stream if continuous ingestion is expected (enables automatic rollover and ILM management).","-"," ---"," ","-## 7. Risk Register","-","-| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |","-|------|-----------|--------|------------|","-| Shard loss during rolling restart | Low | High | Disable allocation before each restart; verify green before next restart |","-| Security enablement breaks existing clients | Medium | High | Update all client credentials/URLs before enabling security; test in staging first |","-| 5 Gi PVC fills during segment merge | Medium | Medium | Check disk usage before upgrade; expand PVCs if <20% headroom |","-| Heap OOM under recovery load | Low | Medium | Increase heap to 1g before upgrade |","-| Pod fails to become Ready after image change | Low | Medium | Keep old image tag in rollback branch; delete the new pod and re-create from old image |","-| `cluster.initial_master_nodes` present on restart causes warn/error | Low | Low | Remove from config during pre-upgrade config restart |","-","----","-","-## 8. Rollback Plan","-","-If the upgrade must be aborted mid-roll:","-","-1. Stop deleting pods.","-2. The already-updated nodes can communicate with 8.11.1 nodes (8.x is wire-compatible within the major version).","-3. Patch the StatefulSet image back to `8.11.1`.","-4. Delete the already-upgraded pods in reverse order to restore the original version.","-5. Verify cluster returns to green.","-","-A mixed-version 8.x cluster is safe for a short period but should not be left in that state longer than a single maintenance window.","-","----","-","-## 9. Approval Gate","-","-This plan must be reviewed and signed off by the SRE lead before any change is applied to the live cluster. The live cluster must remain exactly as described in Section 1 until this plan is approved.","-","-**Checklist before execution:**","-- [ ] SRE lead approval","-- [ ] Snapshot repository configured and pre-upgrade snapshot verified","-- [ ] TLS certificates generated and tested in a non-production environment","-- [ ] Client credential rotation plan in place","-- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled and communicated","-- [ ] On-call engineer available for full duration of rolling upgrade","+*This document is for change-window planning only. The live cluster has not been modified.*"]}],"originalFile":"# Elasticsearch Cluster Upgrade & Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25  \n**Cluster:** `es-cluster` (namespace: `elasticsearch`)  \n**Current version:** 8.11.1  \n**Target version:** 8.17.x (latest stable 8.x release)  \n**Scope:** Planning only — no live changes until this plan is approved.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Cluster Topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Cluster name | es-cluster |\n| Node count | 3 (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2) |\n| Node roles | master + data + ingest (all nodes, no role separation) |\n| Node tier attribute | `node.attr.tier: hot` (uniform) |\n| Pod management | `Parallel` |\n| Update strategy | `OnDelete` (manual pod deletion required to trigger rollout) |\n| Termination grace period | 30 s |\n\n### 1.2 Container Image and Resources\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Image | `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1` |\n| CPU request / limit | 500 m / 1 CPU |\n| Memory request / limit | 1 Gi / 2 Gi |\n| JVM heap | -Xms512m -Xmx512m (fixed, G1GC) |\n| GC collector | G1 Young/Old/Concurrent |\n| Storage per node | 5 Gi PVC (ReadWriteOnce) |\n| OpenJDK version | 21.0.1 (bundled) |\n\n### 1.3 Elasticsearch Configuration (`es-config` ConfigMap)\n\n```yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\n  - es-cluster-0\n  - es-cluster-1\n  - es-cluster-2\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\nxpack.security.enabled: false\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false\n```\n\n### 1.4 Cluster Settings\n\n- **Persistent settings:** none (all defaults)  \n- **Transient settings:** none  \n- Notable defaults in effect: `cluster.routing.allocation.type: desired_balance`, disk watermarks at 85/90/95%, `cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000`.\n\n### 1.5 Cluster Health\n\n- **Status:** green  \n- Active shards: 6 (3 primary + 3 replica)  \n- Pending tasks at inspection: 60 (likely election-related backlog on a fresh cluster)\n\n### 1.6 Indices\n\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Shard allocation |\n|-------|--------|----------|-----------------|\n| audit-index | 3 | 1 | `require.tier: hot`, `_tier_preference: data_content` |\n\nNo data streams, ILM policies, or index templates are associated with user-managed indices. All ILM policies present are built-in Elastic-managed policies (`managed: true`).\n\n### 1.7 Security Posture\n\n| Setting | Value | Risk |\n|---------|-------|------|\n| `xpack.security.enabled` | **false** | CRITICAL — unauthenticated access |\n| HTTP SSL | **false** | Plaintext traffic |\n| Transport SSL | **false** | Plaintext inter-node traffic |\n| Audit logging | false | No access audit trail |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nThese items must be verified and resolved **before** the upgrade window begins.\n\n### 2.1 CRITICAL — Enable Security (Blocking)\n\nElasticsearch 8.x ships with security disabled only when auto-configured on the initial bootstrap; leaving it off permanently in production is unsupported and a compliance risk. **Security must be enabled before upgrading** because:\n\n- Later 8.x releases tighten default security enforcement.\n- The upgrade process itself accesses internal system indices; without security, there is no isolation between internal and user traffic.\n- Any migration to Elasticsearch 9.x will require security to be enabled.\n\n**Required changes to `es-config`:**\n\n```yaml\n# Remove or change these three lines:\nxpack.security.enabled: false          # change to: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false # change to: true (or configure with certificates)\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false # change to: true\n```\n\nSteps to enable security on a running cluster:\n\n1. Generate or obtain TLS certificates for HTTP and transport layers (self-signed CA is acceptable for transport; a valid cert is recommended for HTTP).\n2. Mount the certificates into each pod (add a Secret-backed volume to the StatefulSet).\n3. Update `es-config` with certificate paths and enable security settings.\n4. Perform a full rolling restart (one pod at a time) to apply the new config **before** the version upgrade.\n5. Set the built-in `elastic` superuser password:  \n   `bin/elasticsearch-reset-password -u elastic`\n6. Update any clients (Kibana, application code) with the new credentials and HTTPS endpoints.\n\n### 2.2 Resolve Pending Task Queue\n\nAt inspection the cluster had **60 pending tasks**. Before upgrading:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n  curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/pending_tasks?v\"\n```\n\nInvestigate and resolve any stuck tasks. A high queue depth during an upgrade can cause split-brain or delayed shard re-assignment.\n\n### 2.3 Snapshot Backup\n\nCreate a registered snapshot repository and take a full snapshot of all indices before any change:\n\n```bash\n# Register a repository (adjust type/settings to match your storage backend)\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_snapshot/backup_repo\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n    \"type\": \"fs\",\n    \"settings\": { \"location\": \"/mnt/snapshots\" }\n  }'\n\n# Take snapshot\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_snapshot/backup_repo/pre-upgrade-8.11.1\"\n```\n\nVerify the snapshot completes successfully before proceeding.\n\n### 2.4 Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` After First Bootstrap\n\nThe `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting must be **removed from the config file** after the cluster has completed its initial bootstrapping. Keeping it in place is harmless on a stable cluster but is flagged as a deprecation warning in newer 8.x releases and must be absent for any node that restarts during the upgrade.\n\n**Change to `es-config`:**  \nRemove the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` block entirely.\n\n### 2.5 Shard Allocation Constraint Review\n\n`audit-index` has:\n- `index.routing.allocation.require.tier: hot`\n- `index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference: data_content`\n\nAll three nodes are tagged `node.attr.tier: hot`, so all shards can allocate to any node. This is safe for a rolling upgrade. No changes needed, but **verify allocation is still green** after each node restart during the upgrade.\n\n### 2.6 Storage Headroom\n\nEach node has 5 Gi PVC. Elasticsearch performs segment merges during recovery. Confirm available disk space on each PVC:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec es-cluster-0 -- df -h /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n```\n\nRecommended minimum free space: 20% headroom, or at least 1 Gi above current index size.\n\n### 2.7 Heap Size Assessment\n\nCurrent heap: 512 MB. The 50%-of-container-memory rule (1 Gi request / 2 Gi limit) is not being followed — heap is sized below 50% of the request. For a data node this may cause frequent GC pressure under moderate load.\n\n**Recommended change:**  \nRaise heap to at least `1g` (`-Xms1g -Xmx1g`) and increase the Pod memory request/limit proportionally:\n\n```yaml\n# StatefulSet env\n- name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n  value: \"-Xms1g -Xmx1g\"\n# resources\nresources:\n  requests:\n    cpu: \"500m\"\n    memory: \"2Gi\"\n  limits:\n    cpu: \"2\"\n    memory: \"4Gi\"\n```\n\nApply this in the same rolling restart used to enable security — not a separate disruption.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Procedure (8.11.1 → 8.17.x)\n\nThis is a **rolling upgrade** (no cluster downtime) within the 8.x major series. All 8.x nodes are wire-compatible down to 7.17.0, so a mixed-version cluster is tolerated during the transition.\n\n### Step 1 — Disable Shard Allocation (before each pod restart)\n\n```bash\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n    \"persistent\": {\n      \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"\n    }\n  }'\n```\n\nThis prevents Elasticsearch from re-balancing shards during the brief period a node is offline.\n\n### Step 2 — Perform a Synced Flush\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_flush\"\n```\n\nSynced flush marks shard copies as consistent, which speeds up recovery after the node restarts.\n\n### Step 3 — Update the StatefulSet Image\n\nEdit the StatefulSet to target the new image:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch patch statefulset es-cluster \\\n  --type='json' \\\n  -p='[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/image\",\n         \"value\":\"docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.17.x\"}]'\n```\n\nBecause `updateStrategy: OnDelete`, the StatefulSet will **not** restart any pods automatically.\n\n### Step 4 — Rolling Pod Deletion (one at a time)\n\nDelete pods in reverse ordinal order (es-cluster-2 first, es-cluster-0 last) to minimise master disruption:\n\n```bash\n# Repeat for each pod: 2, 1, 0\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n# Wait for the pod to become Ready before continuing:\nkubectl -n elasticsearch wait pod/es-cluster-2 --for=condition=Ready --timeout=300s\n# Re-enable shard allocation, wait for green:\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\\n  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}'\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=120s\"\n# Verify the restarted node is on the new version:\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"\n# Disable allocation again before the next pod:\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\\n  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"}}'\n# Then: kubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-1\n# Then: kubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-0\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Re-enable Full Shard Allocation\n\nAfter all three pods are updated and the cluster is green:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X PUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d \\\n  '{\"persistent\":{\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}'\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n```bash\n# Cluster health\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?pretty\"\n# All nodes on new version\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master,disk.avail\"\n# Index health\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/indices?v&h=index,health,status,pri,rep,docs.count\"\n# No unassigned shards\ncurl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/shards?v\" | grep UNASSIGNED\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Changes Required in `es-config`\n\nSummarised list of all ConfigMap changes needed (to be applied as a pre-upgrade config restart, before the image upgrade):\n\n```yaml\n# Changes to elasticsearch.yml:\n\n# 1. Enable security (CRITICAL)\nxpack.security.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n\n# 2. Add certificate paths (after generating/mounting certs)\nxpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/http.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/transport.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/transport.p12\n\n# 3. Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes (cluster already bootstrapped)\n# DELETE the following lines:\n# cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n#   - es-cluster-0\n#   - es-cluster-1\n#   - es-cluster-2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Node Role Separation (Recommended for Future Growth)\n\nCurrently all three nodes are `[master, data, ingest]`. This is acceptable for a three-node cluster but introduces risk as the cluster grows: a data-heavy node can starve the master election process.\n\n**Recommended future architecture (requires adding nodes first):**\n\n| Nodes | Roles |\n|-------|-------|\n| es-cluster-0..2 (existing) | `data`, `ingest` |\n| es-master-0..2 (new, small pods) | `master` only (voting_only for 2 of them) |\n\nThis separation is **not required for this upgrade cycle** but should be planned before scaling beyond 5 data nodes.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ILM / Index Template Recommendations\n\nNo user ILM policies are currently active. The `audit-index` has no lifecycle policy attached, meaning its data will accumulate indefinitely.\n\n**Action items for post-upgrade:**\n\n1. Create an ILM policy for `audit-index` with a retention window appropriate for compliance requirements (e.g., 90 days delete, 7-day warm with forcemerge).\n2. Attach the policy: `PUT /audit-index/_settings {\"index.lifecycle.name\": \"<policy-name>\"}`.\n3. Consider converting `audit-index` to a data stream if continuous ingestion is expected (enables automatic rollover and ILM management).\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|------------|\n| Shard loss during rolling restart | Low | High | Disable allocation before each restart; verify green before next restart |\n| Security enablement breaks existing clients | Medium | High | Update all client credentials/URLs before enabling security; test in staging first |\n| 5 Gi PVC fills during segment merge | Medium | Medium | Check disk usage before upgrade; expand PVCs if <20% headroom |\n| Heap OOM under recovery load | Low | Medium | Increase heap to 1g before upgrade |\n| Pod fails to become Ready after image change | Low | Medium | Keep old image tag in rollback branch; delete the new pod and re-create from old image |\n| `cluster.initial_master_nodes` present on restart causes warn/error | Low | Low | Remove from config during pre-upgrade config restart |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Rollback Plan\n\nIf the upgrade must be aborted mid-roll:\n\n1. Stop deleting pods.\n2. The already-updated nodes can communicate with 8.11.1 nodes (8.x is wire-compatible within the major version).\n3. Patch the StatefulSet image back to `8.11.1`.\n4. Delete the already-upgraded pods in reverse order to restore the original version.\n5. Verify cluster returns to green.\n\nA mixed-version 8.x cluster is safe for a short period but should not be left in that state longer than a single maintenance window.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Approval Gate\n\nThis plan must be reviewed and signed off by the SRE lead before any change is applied to the live cluster. The live cluster must remain exactly as described in Section 1 until this plan is approved.\n\n**Checklist before execution:**\n- [ ] SRE lead approval\n- [ ] Snapshot repository configured and pre-upgrade snapshot verified\n- [ ] TLS certificates generated and tested in a non-production environment\n- [ ] Client credential rotation plan in place\n- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled and communicated\n- [ ] On-call engineer available for full duration of rolling upgrade\n","userModified":false}}
